<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1441">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/440.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-09">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I appeal to the kind
                                services of your excellency for the purpose of entreating that you
                                will be good enough to give the necessary orders, with all the
                                despatch which the case requires, for a United States warship to be
                                sent to Mazatlan, if possible, for the protection of Spanish
                                subjects resident at that place.</p>
                            <p>I am informed by telegraphic despatches just received, that these
                                people are being subjected to fresh acts of injustice at the hands
                                of the Constitutionalist forces, who have also arrested the Spanish
                                Consular Agent at that port.</p>
                            <p>Expressing, in anticipation, to your excellency my sincere
                                thanks,</p>
                            <p>I take [etc.].</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>